external_knowledge:
- Timeframes refer to different periods used in financial or time-series data analysis;
- Common timeframes include 1 minute, 5 minutes, 15 minutes, 1 hour, 1 day, etc.;
- The `interval_minutes` column specifies the duration of each timeframe in minutes.

sql:
SELECT timeframe_name, interval_minutes
FROM timeframes
ORDER BY interval_minutes DESC;

